raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert II
raw_data.description: Demonstrated experience in analyzing complex requirements and recommending the development of effective strategies. Assists in creating strategic plans and concepts while coordinating and managing the preparation of analyses, evaluations, and recommendations. Ensures proper implementation of programs and system specifications in areas such as risk management, life-cycle management, policy development, methodologies, and modeling within the relevant functional areas.  In addition to core subject matter expertise, the SME II collaborates with communications teams to advise on marketing, advertising, and public relations strategies that enhance organizational visibility and stakeholder engagement. By leveraging strong analytical, creative, and organizational skills, the SME II supports the successful execution of initiatives and the development of innovative solutions aligned with both programmatic and outreach objectives.
